    "intro": "Interpretation moves from what the text says to what it means — tracing the author's intent in its original redemptive-historical context. Genesis 31 is both a family narrative and a theological argument about the covenant God's governance of His servant's life. The four movements below follow the chapter's pericope structure, attending to the flow of argument, the ancient Near Eastern background, and the chapter's place in the larger Jacob cycle.",
